<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{title}} - Deno App</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <nav id="main-nav">
      <a href="/" class="brand-logo" id="brand-logo">
        <span class="brand-icon"></span>
        <span class="brand-text">AGILE</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/about" id="nav-about">About</a>
      <div class="dropdown">
        <a href="#" class="dropbtn" id="nav-resources">Resources â–¼</a>
        <div class="dropdown-content">
          <a href="/resources/documentation" id="nav-resources-docs">Documentation</a>
          <a href="/resources/tutorials" id="nav-resources-tutorials">Tutorials</a>
          <a href="/resources/support" id="nav-resources-support">Support</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      {{#if isAdmin}}
        <a href="/admin/users" id="nav-admin-users">Users</a>
        <a href="/admin/roles" id="nav-admin-roles">Roles</a>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if isLoggedIn}}
        <a href="/logout" class="nav-right" id="nav-logout">Logout</a>
      {{else}}
        <a href="/login" class="nav-right" id="nav-login">Login</a>
      {{/if}}
    </nav>
    
    {{#if isLoggedIn}}
      <div class="user-info" id="user-info-display">Logged in as: {{user.email}}</div>
    {{/if}}
    
    <h1 id="page-title">{{title}}</h1>
    
    <div class="content-section">
      <h2>Get Help & Support</h2>
      <p>Need assistance? We're here to help!</p>
      
      <div class="support-section">
        <h3>ðŸ“š Common Issues</h3>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: I can't log in with my credentials</h4>
          <p>A: Ensure you're using the correct email and password. If you recently migrated passwords, try logging in again as passwords are automatically upgraded to bcrypt on first login.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: How do I reset a user's password?</h4>
          <p>A: As an admin, go to Users, click Edit on the user, enter a new password, and click Update User.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: Can I delete the admin user?</h4>
          <p>A: No, the primary admin user (admin@example.com) cannot be deleted to ensure system access. You also cannot delete the last remaining admin user.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: Tests are failing with connection errors</h4>
          <p>A: Make sure the application is running on localhost:8000 before running tests. Start it with <code>deno task start</code> in a separate terminal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="support-section">
        <h3>ðŸ”§ Troubleshooting</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Database Connection Issues:</strong> Check your .env file and ensure MySQL is running</li>
          <li><strong>Permission Errors:</strong> Verify you have the correct roles assigned</li>
          <li><strong>Session Expired:</strong> Log out and log back in to refresh your session</li>
          <li><strong>ChromeDriver Errors:</strong> Install ChromeDriver for your system to run Selenium tests</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="support-section">
        <h3>ðŸ“ž Contact Information</h3>
        <div class="contact-card">
          <p><strong>Technical Support:</strong> support@example.com</p>
          <p><strong>Documentation:</strong> See the Documentation page</p>
          <p><strong>GitHub Issues:</strong> Report bugs and feature requests</p>
          <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> Within 24 hours</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="support-section">
        <h3>ðŸ’¡ Quick Tips</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use <code>deno task dev</code> for development with auto-reload</li>
          <li>Run <code>deno task migrate-passwords</code> to upgrade password security</li>
          <li>Check the README.md for setup instructions</li>
          <li>All element IDs are documented for Selenium testing</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
